{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Cut each calamari hood into half lengthways. Cut each piece in half horizontally and then cut into strips (approx. 1.5 cm wide). Transfer calamari strips into a ceramic or glass bowl with the prawns and set aside.","Place garlic, lemon zest, chilli, parsley and coriander into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl again with spatula.","Add olive oil, wine, paprika and salt and sauté <nobr>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add ⅓ of the calamari and prawns and cook <nobr>1-2 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <\/nobr>, or until cooked to your liking. Using tongs, carefully remove calamari and prawns from mixing bowl and transfer into a thermal serving bowl or warm ceramic dish and cover to keep warm. Leave the oil and herb mixture in mixing bowl.","Add ⅓ of the calamari and prawns and cook <nobr>1-2 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <\/nobr>, or until cooked to your liking. Carefully remove calamari and prawns and transfer into bowl with the previous batch. Leave the oil and herb mixture in mixing bowl.","Add remaining ⅓ of the calamari and prawns and cook <nobr>1-2 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <\/nobr>, or until cooked to your liking. Carefully remove calamari and prawns and transfer into bowl with the previous batch, then transfer the oil and herb mixture into a serving jug.","Squeeze 1-2 lemon wedges over seafood and garnish with extra chopped herbs. Drizzle with the reserved hot oil and herb mixture and serve immediately with extra lemon wedges on the side."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["3 calamari hoods (approx. 330 g total)","20 raw prawns, deveined and tails intact","4 garlic cloves","2 pieces lemon zest (approx. 5 x 2 cm), no white pith","½ - 1 long red chilli, deseeded if preferred and cut into halves","3 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only, plus extra finely chopped for garnishing","3 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only, plus extra finely chopped for garnishing","40 g olive oil","2 - 3 tbsp dry white wine","½ tsp sweet paprika","¼ tsp sea salt, to taste","1 - 2 lemons, cut into wedges, to serve"]}],"id":"r82194","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-y9No5agBFxc\/XZMuo93hLjI\/AAAAAAAAaH0\/LkywSZrj86ULkLasKARu5qT3z9_sVXH_ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_NYJoj1D8V8d5WCha.png","title":"Spiced garlic prawns and calamari","publishedAt":"2015-05-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"17 g","fat":"5.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"0.8 g","calories":"543 kJ \/ 129 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ceramic or glass bowl, tongs, thermal serving bowl or warm ceramic dish, serving jug","hintsAndTricks":["This recipe is best when served immediately, so we recommend pre-preparing all of your ingredients, including garnishes, before you commence cooking your seafood in steps 4-7."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","15m","8 portions"]}